    "title": "Opinion Announcement - January 14, 2014",
    "transcript": {
        "title": null,
        "duration": 230.016,
        "sections": [
            {
                "start": 0,
                "stop": 230.016,
                "byte_start": 106496,
                "byte_stop": 0,
                "turns": [
                    {
                        "start": 0,
                        "stop": 9.324,
                        "byte_start": 106496,
                        "byte_stop": 143799,
                        "speaker": null,
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 9.324,
                                "byte_start": 106496,
                                "byte_stop": 143799,
                                "text": "Justice Sotomayor has our opinion this morning in case 12-1036 Mississippi v. AU Optronics Corporation."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 9.324,
                        "stop": 230.016,
                        "byte_start": 143799,
                        "byte_stop": 0,
                        "speaker": null,
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 9.324,
                                "stop": 20.812,
                                "byte_start": 143799,
                                "byte_stop": 189774,
                                "text": "The State of Mississippi sued a group of LCD manufacturers alleging that they had engaged in a price fixing scheme in violation of state law."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 20.812,
                                "stop": 31.009,
                                "byte_start": 189774,
                                "byte_stop": 230630,
                                "text": "The manufacturers removed the case to federal court on the theory that on a theory that the sued is a mass action onto the Class Action Fairness Act or the Act."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 31.009,
                                "stop": 47.918,
                                "byte_start": 230630,
                                "byte_stop": 298235,
                                "text": "The act to find mass action to mean any civil action in which monetary relief claims of 100 or more persons are propose to be tried jointly on the ground that the plaintiffs claims involved common questions."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 47.918,
                                "stop": 54.107,
                                "byte_start": 298235,
                                "byte_stop": 322999,
                                "text": "The issue presented is whether Mississippi\u2019s lawsuit is a mass action so define."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 54.107,
                                "stop": 75.962,
                                "byte_start": 322999,
                                "byte_stop": 410352,
                                "text": "The Court of Appeals held that it is reasoning that even though the state is the sole named plaintiff to the suit, the suit -- the states complaint includes a claim for restitution based on LCD purchases made by 100 or more unidentified Mississippi citizens."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 75.962,
                                "stop": 92.924,
                                "byte_start": 410352,
                                "byte_stop": 478271,
                                "text": "In doing so, the Court of Appeals believed that it was required to look pass the number of plaintiffs on the face of the complaint and determine if there are 100 or more unnamed persons who are real parties and interest to the suit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 92.924,
                                "stop": 94.585,
                                "byte_start": 478271,
                                "byte_stop": 484854,
                                "text": "We reverse."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 94.585,
                                "stop": 105.083,
                                "byte_start": 484854,
                                "byte_stop": 526858,
                                "text": "The Act does not define a mass action to include suits involving monetary claims of 100 or more unnamed real parties and interest."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 105.083,
                                "stop": 135.717,
                                "byte_start": 526858,
                                "byte_stop": 649425,
                                "text": "It instead defines a mass action to include cases involving claims of 100 or more persons that are proposed to be tried jointly on the ground that the plaintiffs\u0027 claims involved common questions that, that definition makes clear that the 100 or more persons at issue are the proposed plaintiffs themselves not some unspecified individuals who lack any participation in the suit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 135.717,
                                "stop": 151.165,
                                "byte_start": 649425,
                                "byte_stop": 711178,
                                "text": "Interpreting the provision to require 100 or more named plaintiffs is consistent with the language used in Rule 20 of the Federal Rules of Civil Procedure, a rule we presume Congress was aware of when it drafted the Act."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 151.165,
                                "stop": 160.179,
                                "byte_start": 711178,
                                "byte_stop": 747227,
                                "text": "Like the mass action provision Rule 20 discusses persons who propose to join in one action as plaintiffs."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 160.179,
                                "stop": 173.78,
                                "byte_start": 747227,
                                "byte_stop": 801667,
                                "text": "Our holding also avoids the many administrative difficulties that would arise if the provision were construed to require identifying every single unnamed individual with an interest in a suit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 173.78,
                                "stop": 186.699,
                                "byte_start": 801667,
                                "byte_stop": 853389,
                                "text": "And although we have required an inquiry into unnamed real parties at interest and other context, we decline to do so here where the text of the Act commands otherwise."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 186.699,
                                "stop": 207.105,
                                "byte_start": 853389,
                                "byte_stop": 934996,
                                "text": "We therefore hope -- therefore hold that to qualify as a mass action under the plain meaning of the statue, an action must involved monetary claims brought my 100 or more proposed plaintiffs who propose to try their claims jointly in a single trial."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 207.105,
                                "stop": 212.877,
                                "byte_start": 934996,
                                "byte_stop": 958088,
                                "text": "Here there are not 100 name plaintiffs but one, the State of Mississippi."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 212.877,
                                "stop": 217.12,
                                "byte_start": 958088,
                                "byte_stop": 975015,
                                "text": "So the case is not a mass action removable under the Act."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 217.12,
                                "stop": 227.511,
                                "byte_start": 975015,
                                "byte_stop": 1016602,
                                "text": "The judgment of the United States Court of Appeals for the Fifth Circuit is accordingly reversed and the cases remanded for further proceedings consistent with this opinion."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 227.511,
                                "stop": 230.016,
                                "byte_start": 1016602,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The opinion is for unanimous court."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
    },
